  "lesson": {
    "title": "Adjustable RC Delay",
    "description": "Same RC delay idea as lesson 23, but the fixed 4.7kΩ is replaced by a 470Ω safety resistor plus a potentiometer (90° in the center column). Press the tact button and turn the knob — more resistance = slower fade-on and fade-off (larger τ), less resistance = faster. Cap center, LED east at 90°; cap + toward power."
  },
